{% extends 'layout.twig' %}

{% block body %}
    <article class="article">
        <header class="article__header">
            <div class="artiсle__header-title">Hawk.io</div>
            <div class="artiсle__header-caption">Fast and lightweight errors tracking service</div>
        </header>
        <h1>Platform documentation</h1>
        <p>Hawk.io is a clever and easy-to-use error tracker. It collects all your code exceptions and errors and help you to improve applications</p>
        <p>Please, welcome to our simple user guide.</p>

        <h2>Gettign Started</h2>
        <p>Integration scheme contains three steps. Your need to register, add domain and install one of our catchers.</p>

        <h3>Create an account</h3>
        <p>Follow by <a href="/join">/join</a> link to access registration form. Leave working email, and we send your password to this. You can change it at any  time later.</p>
        <p>After this you’ll entrance an internal section. We call it Garage.</p>

        <h3>Register domains</h3>
        <p>Now, look at the sidebar. There will be appears all your registered domains. Touch «<a href="/websites/create">Add domain</a>» button to create your first.</p>
        <p>Fill domain name and submit form. You are beatiful, that’s it.</p>

        <h2>Integration</h2>
        <p>All registration procedures passed, next is installation some error Catchers. It is simple scripts, that collects exceptions and delivers them to Garage.</p>

        <h3>Add server handler</h3>
        <p>Currently, we provide Catchers for the next languages:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>PHP</li>
            <li>Node.js</li>
            <li>Python</li>
        </ul>
        <p>This list will be expanded soon. If you can code, you can implement your own Catcher.</p>

        <h3>Add client handler</h3>
        <p>To deliver JavaScript errors we provide fast and non-blocking Socket-based Catcher.</p>
        <p><a href="https://github.com/codex-team/hawk.client">Get JavaScript Catcher</a></p>
        <p>How to use. Include <abbr title="HTML script tag">script</abbr>tag loaded from CDN or local cloned from repository examplar.</p>
        <p>
            <pre>
                &lt;script src="hawk.js" async&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
            </pre>
        </p>
        <p>Next, initialize module with your Token.</p>
        <p>
            <pre>
                &lt;script&gt;
                    hawk.init(“Your Token”);
                &lt;/script&gt;
            </pre>
        </p>
    </article>
{% endblock %}
